						               													<description>Genius Loci is a two-player combinatorial game played on a hexagonal board. According to the Romans, a genius loci is the spirit of a place; in this game, the spirits allow movement between places.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playing pieces consist of men, in two colours, belonging to the players; and gods - neutral pieces which can neither capture nor be captured, but enable the movement of the other pieces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn consists of the following steps:&amp;#10;(a) optional - move a god&amp;#10;(b) required - make a sacrifice; move a man of your colour according to the rules of a god, so as to capture another piece (a sacrifice)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a player may not make a sacrifice on their turn.  They lose.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is inspired by the &amp;quot;Activator Piece&amp;quot; discussions in the BGG abstract games forums.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
